uhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aDie Beschreibung und Analyse sprachlicher Variation gehört zu den Feldern, die in der germanistischen Sprachwissenschaft in jüngerer Zeit stark an Aufmerksamkeit gewonnen haben. Dieser Band zeigt in einer Zusammenschau verschiedener Ansätze von der Einstellungs- bis zur Sprachkontaktforschung, wie sich Variation entlang verschiedener Normorientierungen von Sprechern sowie als Ergebnis von Identitätskonstruktionen begreifen lässt.  aThe description and analysis of language variation has taken on increased importance in German linguistics in recent years. This volume reviews different approaches, including research on attitudes and on language contact, in order to explore how variations can be understood in terms of speakers' different normative perspectives and as a product of identity constructions.  afunded by Leibniz-Institut für Deutsche Sprache  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aGerman languagexStandardization. 0aGerman languagexVariation. 4aDialektologie. 4aIdentität. 4aSprachkontakt. 4aSprachvariation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDialectology.  aidentity.  alanguage contact.  alanguage variation.1 aPlewnia, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenz, Alexandra N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdler, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiehl, Claudia Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnipf-Komlósi, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go